"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-05-Dominican-athlete-Thea-LaFond-discusses-her-historic-Olympic-win-1vO8pYozCGk-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Dan Williams  Copied  The 2024 Paris Olympic Games has seen a number of firsts, especially for islands in the Caribbean Sea.\\u00a0 First, Julien Alfred won Saint Lucia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s first ever Olympic medal when she won gold in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100-meter final.  And then, Thea LaFond, won gold in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s triple jump, a first too for the island of Dominica. An impressive achievement considering the island doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t even have an athletics track.  CGTN\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Dan Williams sat down with LaFond to talk about what her success could mean for the island.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"